<HEADLINE> UK, Top Destination For Investment In Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Britain remains the top destination
for foreign investment in Europe in the past year despite the
strong pound, financial crisis in Asia and its decision to stay
out of euro now.
</P>
<P>
More than 650 new projects were announced Wednesday in Britain
Bureau's Annual Review of Operation 1999, and the UK's global
investment stock now stands at 196 billion pounds, an increase of
30 percent on the 1998 figure.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also show that those projects directly created
44,000 new jobs, with the knock-on effect of another 118,000 in
associated businesses.
</P>
<P>
The key sectors were software, telecommunications and the car
industry. Trade and Industry Secretary Stephen Byers said at the
launch of the Review, this showed that the UK was developing a
high-tech character which attracted leading edge investors.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on this achievement, Foreign Secretary Robin Cook
said, "Investment from overseas creates British jobs, revitalizes
regional economies and fuels British prosperity."
</P>
<P>
"Persuading foreign investors to come to Britain ensures we
stay competitive in the global economy," Cook added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
