<HEADLINE> Albanian, Greek, Macedonian FMs Meet to Discuss Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The foreign ministers of Albania,
Greece and Macedonia met in the Prespa Lake area Wednesday to
discuss economic cooperation projects among their countries.
</P>
<P>
The three ministers discussed joint projects on infrastructure,
including integration of roads, railways, electropower
transmission lines, and gas pipelines, Albanian Foreign Minister
Paskal Milo told a press conference here upon returning from the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Milo said that he had presented at the meeting four priority
projects proposed by the Albanian government, including Corridor
8, a road network project designed to link Durres in Albania,
Skopje in Macedonia and Sofia in Bulgaria, and a regional energy
network linking Albania, Macedonia and Greece with high tension
lines and gas pipelines.
</P>
<P>
Macedonian Foreign Minister Aleksandar Dimitrov and Greek
Foreign Minister George Papandreou attended the gathering at Saint
Akilio on the Greek side of the lake area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
