<HEADLINE> Uganda to Set Up Chinese Business Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's Second Deputy Prime
Minister and Minister of Tourism,Trade and Industry Moses Ali
announced here Wednesday plans to set up a Chinese business center
in capital Kampala.
</P>
<P>
Ali, upon his return from a working visit to China Wednesday,
told a press conference that the center will reduce overhead
transport costs currently being encountered by Ugandan business
people who import Chinese goods for sale in Uganda.
</P>
<P>
During his China visit, Ali held discussions with several
international companies and business personalities with a view of
establishing joint ventures with their Ugandan counterparts.
</P>
<P>
He was accompanied to China by Gerald Sendaula, Minister of
Finance, Planning and Economic Development.  
