<HEADLINE> Chirac Promises Barak Support in Search for Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
promised Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak Wednesday that France
would bring him all his support in the search for peace in the
Middle East.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone conversation with Barak, Chirac said that "some
changes have already taken place" since the new prime minister
came to power, according to presidential spokeswoman Catherine
Colonna.
</P>
<P>
Chirac also said that to re-establish a "strong and confiding
relationship" with Israel is one of his priorities, and he invited
Barak to visit France at a time of his convenience.
</P>
<P>
Barak, who called Chirac before he began a visit to the United
States Wednesday, said that he is determined to go ahead in the
peace process, said the French presidential spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
Relations between France and Israel remained strained during
the rule of former Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu,
because of differences over Israel's policy toward the
Palestinians, Israel's construction of Jewish settlements as well
as the status of the eastern part of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
France was also critical of Israel's occupation of southern
Lebanon and condemned Israel's air raids against Lebanon last
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
