<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Donates Food to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The United States is to
provide 31,000 metric tons of emergency food assistance to
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed here by the U.S. Ambassador to
Ethiopia David Shinn and Judith Lewis, representative of the World
Food Program (WFP), the Ethiopian News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The food donation, valued at 13.52 million U.S. dollars, will
be distributed mainly to mal-nourished children, lactating mothers
and pregnant women, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The WFP approved on June 1 this year an emergency operation to
provide 40.5 million U.S. dollars of food assistance to 1.2
million Ethiopians affected by food shortage.
</P>
<P>
Parts of Ethiopia reportedly failed to have enough rain in
small rainy season from February to May this year, which has
caused the grain shortage. 
</P>
