On Thursday, Cohen will hold talks with Turkish Prime Minister
Bulent Ecevit, Deputy Prime Minister Devlet Bahceli and Defense
Minister Sabahattin Cakmakoglu on the latest developments in the
Middle East peace process, the Balkans and the Caucasus.
</P>
<P>
Cohen and Turkish high-ranking officials will also discuss the
thorny relations between Turkey and Greece, the Cyprus problem
and the situation in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Cohen's visit to Turkey is part of his six-leg tour which will
also takes him to Greece, Norway, Denmark, Hungary and
Albania. 
