<HEADLINE> Public Approval Rate For Japanese Cabinet Up to 57.2 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Public support rate for Japanese
cabinet rose to 57.2 percent, up 7 percentage points from the
previous survey in May, showed a Kyodo News survey released
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The survey also indicated that the percentage disapproving of
the Japanese cabinet fell to 34.1 percent from 39.9 percent in the
previous poll.
</P>
<P>
The latest survey was conducted on 3,000 people aged 20 or
above nationwide through interviews Saturday and Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Asked to cite reasons for why they support the cabinet, 44.8
percent replied there is no appropriate alternative to the current
premier while 26 percent said they have confidence in the prime
minister.
</P>
<P>
Those who said they had confidence in the cabinet's ability to
create economic policies to pull Japan out of the current economic
downturn rose to 8.4 percent from 7.0 percent, reflecting support
for the cabinet's recent efforts to boost industry and employment.
</P>
