<HEADLINE> China, Portugal Agree on Macao Transfer Media Arrangements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- China and Portugal reached
agreement here Wednesday on media arrangements for the transfer
ceremony of Macao.
</P>
<P>
A release issued by the Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group
said that the two sides deem the transfer ceremony as an important
event jointly held by the government of the People's Republic of
China and the government of the Republic of Portugal and welcome
journalists from media institutions from all over the world to
cover the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have decided to entrust the Macao government to
process journalists' applications for covering the ceremony and
handle matters relating to media coverage in accordance with
internationally accepted practices.
</P>
<P>
According to the arrangements, media organizations interested
in covering the ceremony should submit applications along with the
personal particulars of their representatives to the Macao
government through the Ceremony's Coordination Office before
October 29, 1999. The Coordination Office will start to distribute
application forms on August 2, 1999, the notice said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also decided to establish a press and broadcast
center to facilitate media coverage of the ceremony and welcome
all media organizations to use the center.
</P>
<P>
Macao from zero hour of December 20 this year will return to
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
