<HEADLINE> Belgian Prosecutor Shoots Himself to Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A Belgian public prosecutor has
shot himself to death, said local media reports Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The prosecutor was responsible for investigating Belgium's
paedophile scandal and the murder of a former Socialist Party
patriarch committed suicide Tuesday, according to local TV and
radio reports.
</P>
<P>
Hubert Massa, 54, was in charge of investigations into the
deaths of four young girls seized by convicted paedophile Marc
Dutroux and the mafia-like murder in 1991 of the French-speaking
Socialist Party leader Andre Cools.
</P>
<P>
The probe into Cools' killing uncovered a bribes-for-contracts
scandal which triggered the resignation of the then NATO secretary
general, Belgium's former Deputy Prime Minister Willy Claes.
</P>
<P>
Massa's officemates gave no motive for his suicide, the media
reports said. And investigation into the suicide is expected to be
launched soon. 
</P>
