<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, July 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak pledged to comply
with all agreements his country had signed with the Palestinians
as part of the efforts to revive the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
He made the pledge Tuesday night during his talks with
Jordanian King Abdullah Bin Hussein at the southern port city of
Aqaba of the desert kingdom.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Barak also voiced hope to resume Israel's
peace talks with Syria, the semi-official Jordan Times reported.
(BC-Jordan-Israel-Peace)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- The new Kuwaiti cabinet, which includes a
mixture of old and new faces, liberal and tribal figures, and most
notably a strong economic team, was sworn in on Wednesday before
Emir Sheikh Jaber Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah.
</P>
<P>
The 16-member cabinet was appointed by the Emir on Tuesday
following the resignation of the last cabinet ten days ago.
(BC-Kuwait-Cabinet)
</P>
