JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak left for
Washington Wednesday for his first trip to the U.S. aimed at
restoring trust and intimacy between Israel and its closest ally
and coordinating positions on reviving the stalled Middle East
peace process.
</P>
<P>
