Nationalists, that we have come too far in this process, there is
too much at stake, to allow the issues that divide them to bring
this process down," Lockhart said.
</P>
<P>
The Good Friday pact, calling for the creation of an all-party
regional assembly to take over many of the tasks of governing the
province from London, was snagged by a dispute over guerrilla
disarmament.
</P>
<P>
The pro-British Unionists insisted the Irish Republican Army
(IRA) begin to disarm before its political wing Sinn Fein is
permitted to take part in the provincial government. Sinn Fein
rejected the demand. 
