Planetel Communications Ltd, a partner with Vodacom of South
Africa.
</P>
<P>
The licensing of Planetel Communication Limited, the fourth
land mobile cellular operator in Tanzania, was approved by TCC
members at a meeting in the city last week.
</P>
<P>
Planetel Communication Limited, based in Dar es Salaam, is
licensed to install, operate, maintain and exploit the global
system for mobile, public land mobile network and provide services
in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Jacqueline Peter Noni, the managing director of Planetel
Communication Limited, said that access to Vodacom's support and
facilities will ensure world-class services in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Companies that have been issued land mobile cellular phone
licenses are Tritel, MIC (Tanzania) Limited, and Tanzania
Telecommunication Company Limited.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also approved three public data communications
operators and nine Internet providers, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The licensing of new operators is intended to increase the
telephone density, improve the quality of services and reduce
tariffs through competition. 
