<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Fisherman Dies of Shark Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A Tanzanian fisherman has
been killed after being badly wounded by a shark in the Indian
Ocean, hospital sources said.
</P>
<P>
Abdallah Jamal, 30, was injured by the shark on his right hand,
buttocks and throat Monday in the capital Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
He was then rushed to the Muhimbili Medical Center but died
there Tuesday night, Almas Jumaa, a press officer at the
hospital, said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
