<HEADLINE> Annan to Present Vienna Civil Society Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan will be presenting the first Vienna Civil Society Award,
which honors individuals or groups for outstanding work in
fighting global crime and drug abuse, to four international
winners at a Vienna ceremony on July 19, U.N. officials announced
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The winners, selected by a 10-member international committee
from a list of more than 100 nominations worldwide, include the
Foundation Azteca of Mexico, Shanthi Ranganathan of India, the
Drug Abuse Prevention Center of Japan and Rogers Kasirye of
Uganda, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
The Vienna Civil Society Award was jointly created and
co-sponsored by the Office for Drug Control and Crime Prevention
(ODCCP), the Austrian Government and the City of Vienna. It marks
the first time the United Nations will honor individuals,
institutions and organizations helping to fight global crime, drug
abuse and terrorism.  
