<HEADLINE> Record Number Of People Crossing China's Borders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
 BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua)-- The number of people exiting and
entering China across its borders was almost 78 million in the
first half of this year, a new record, and 14.45 percent more than
that for the same period last year, the Ministry of Public
Security announced here today.
</P>
<P>
 The Ministry's Exit-Entry Administration said that the number
of Chinese mainlanders crossing border checks increased 7.64
percent to 8.7 million, Hong Kong and Macao residents by 15.37
percent to 59 million, and Taiwan residents up 19.36 to reach 2.4
million.
</P>
<P>
 The number of foreigners was up 14 percent to 7.6 million.
</P>
<P>
 The top ten destinations of Chinese mainlanders were: Hong
Kong, Macao, Thailand, Japan, Russia, the United States, the
Republic of Korea, Singapore, the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
 The top ten countries with the most travelers to China were:
Japan, the Republic of Korea, the United States, Russia, Malaysia,
Singapore, Mongolia, the Philippines, Britain and Thailand.
</P>
</TEXT>
