<HEADLINE> Mongolian President Reiterates "One China" Stance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, Mongolia, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian President
Nachagyn Bagabandy reiterated here Thursday afternoon that
Mongolia adheres to its principled stance on the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
Bagabandy told visiting Chinese President Jiang Zemin during
their talks that "There is only one China in the world and Taiwan
is an inalienable part of the Chinese territory. The government of
the People's Republic of China is the sole legitimate government
representing the whole China."
</P>
<P>
Jiang recalled his explanation to Bagabandy about China's
stance on the Taiwan issue during his visit to China last December.
</P>
<P>
Bagabandy then in return expressed his understanding and
agreement of China's stand, stressing that Mongolia supported
China's principle of "One country, two systems; and Peaceful
reunification" and did not support the independence of Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his appreciation of the stand taken by the
Mongolian government and believed the Mongolian side will continue
to stick to its correct stance.  
</P>
