<HEADLINE> Foreigners Suspected Of Committing Crimes In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the Beijing Public
Security Bureau said today that some foreigners have recently
committed a number of thefts, robberies, acts of swindling or
other crimes in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
By mid-July, Beijing police had investigated 46 such cases,
mostly in shops, hotels, clothes markets, and booking offices.
</P>
<P>
The suspects often used foreign currency exchange or asking for
change as a cover.In one case, on July 7, a foreigner went to a
market in Fengtai District in southwestern Beijing to buy some
cloth and took 8,000 yuan (about 960 U.S. dollars) from the
peddler when the man went to get change for him.
</P>
<P>
Beijing police have reminded people, especially shopkeepers at
the local level to be on the alert against foreign criminals and
to help police stop these crimes.
</P>
<P>
There are now 25 people from Africa, Southeast Asia, Europe,
and America serving time in Beijing, according to Beijing Youth
Daily, mostly for fraud, violence, rape, or trying to get state
secrets. 
</P>
