<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Vaccine Company's Donations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- France's Pasteur Merieux Connaught
has made a vaccine donation to protect some 1,000 senior citizens
in Beijing from pneumococcal pneumonia.
</P>
<P>
It also donated 1.6 million yuan worth of vaccine for the
elderly in 8 other Chinese cities today.
</P>
<P>
At least a million people around the world are killed by
pneumonia caused by pneumococcus bacteria, which can also lead to
other illnesses like spinal meningitis, pleuritis, and myocarditis.
Vaccination is the best way to prevent pneumococcal pneumonia,
because the overuse of antibiotics has resulted in drug resistance.
</P>
<P>
China has at least 2.5 million cases of pneumonia annually and
125,000 deaths as a result of pneumococcal infection. The death
rate of pneumococcal pneumonia is as high as 28.6 percent among
people over the age of 50.
</P>
<P>
Pasteur Merieux Connaught has donated typhoid fever vaccines
and hepatitis A vaccines in the past two years, according to the
company's managing director for China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
