<HEADLINE> Interior Decoration Becoming More Popular In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Interior decoration is increasing
in popularity in China, where 95 billion yuan worth of business is
done annually in decoration projects.
</P>
<P>
More than 95 percent of the country's newly-built homes have
had decoration work.
</P>
<P>
In addition to paying more attention to food, clothing,
entertainment and cars, the ordinary Chinese are now spending more
on home decorations. In big cities like Beijing, Shanghai,
Guangzhou, Harbin, Nanjing, Shenzhen, Dalian and Chengdu, this is
especially true.
</P>
<P>
China's urbanites have decorated their homes at an average cost
of at least 20,000 yuan. Total sales of home decoration materials
in Beijing exceeded 2 billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
Experts here expect that by the year 2002, the country's total
housing floor space will exceed 5 billion square meters, and a
potential total of 83 million apartment units will be decorated,
at a total cost of 30 billion yuan each year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
