<HEADLINE> China to Hold First Actuary Qualification Exam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China will hold its first actuary
qualification examination on October 6, the China Insurance
Regulatory Commission (CIRC) announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The CIRC said it will accept applications for the exam from
July 20 to August 15.
</P>
<P>
Actuaries plays an important role in the operation of insurance
firms, which depend on actuaries to statistically calculate risks
and premiums.
</P>
<P>
As China's insurance sector has been growing at an annual rate
of nearly 30 percent in the last decade, the country is in need of
many qualified actuaries. The training of actuaries in China began
only as recently as 1991, and to date there are about 180
graduates qualified to perform this function, according to Zhang
Lianghua, an official with the CIRC Life Insurance Department.
</P>
<P>
</P>
