<HEADLINE> China Hopes Ties With PNG Back To Normal (more added) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China today expressed the hope
that the new government of Papua New Guinea (PNG) will reverse its
predecessor's decision to establish "diplomatic ties" with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Only by so doing can relations between China and Papua New
Guinea be brought back on to a normal track, Foreign Ministry
spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue said at a regular press conference here
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that China congratulates Mekere Morauta on his
election yesterday as Papua New Guinea's new prime minister.
</P>
<P>
She said China has attached great importance to friendly and
cooperative relations with PNG, adding that since China and PNG
forged diplomatic ties in 1976, their friendly and cooperative
relationship has conformed to the long-term and fundamental
interests of the peoples of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
She noted that Taiwan has been a part of China from ancient
times and that the People's Republic of China is the sole
legitimate government representing the whole of China, adding that
"the government of PNG made a clear commitment on this when it
established diplomatic ties with China."
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang, the erroneous decision of the former PNG
leader to sign a so-called communique on the establishment of "
diplomatic ties" with Taiwan has been strongly opposed by the
people of PNG.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
