<HEADLINE> China Seeks Breakthrough in Developing Manned Space Flight Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China seeks to achieve a
breakthrough in its researches on manned space travel technology
in the near future.
</P>
<P>
"We will try to have a breakthrough in this technological
research by the end of this century or the beginning of the next
century," said Zhang Lihui, director of the Research and
Development Department of the China Aerospace Science and
Technology Corporation (CASTC), at a press conference given by the
Information Office of the State Council here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhang made this response when answering a question on when
China will launch a manned spaceship. The press conference was
held to further refute the "Cox Report" concocted by the Select
Committee of the U.S. House of Representatives.
</P>
<P>
She said that in 1992 the State Council approved a medium- and
long-term guideline for the development of science and technology
during the 2000 to 2020 period.
</P>
<P>
According to the guidelines, China will initiate research and
development in the field of manned space flight technology to
guarantee its international status in the aerospace industry.
</P>
<P>
"What I can tell you is that China's research institutes,
universities, and CASTC have started the study of relevant
research in this aspect," Zhang said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
