<HEADLINE> Cooperation Potential for France And China in Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- A senior French official has said
that there is great potential for France and China to cooperate in
agricultural research.
</P>
<P>
Claude Bernet, General Director for Education and Research in
the Agricultural Ministry of France, said Wednesday that both
France, the world's largest farm-produce processing country, and
China, the world's most populous country, are facing the problem
of improving the quality of agricultural products and protecting
the environment.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation between the two nations can be significant despite
their climatic and cultural differences said Bernet, who is now in
Kunming, the capital of southwest China's Yunnan Province, to
participate in the '99 Kunming World Horticulture Exposition.
</P>
<P>
Bernet expressed the hope that long-term and regular exchanges
of technical personnel will be conducted between China and France.
</P>
<P>
Thus far, about 20 French agricultural research institutions
have established ties with Chinese research institutions, he said.
</P>
<P>
The French National Institute for Research in Agronomy and Food
Industry has trained hundreds of researchers for China, and some
40 Chinese scientists are now receiving training or working at the
institute, which has had a cooperative relationship with China for
20 years.
</P>
<P>
According to Philippe Ferlin, director of the institute's
International Relations Department, later this year the institute
will sponsor a project aimed at preventing orange and tangerine
tree diseases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
