<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Spokeswoman on Sino-ASEAN Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China and ASEAN nations would
conduct "friendly and in-depth" exchange of views on the fresh
changes in international and regional situation, as well as the
development of the ASEAN Regional Forum (ARF), Chinese Foreign
Ministry Spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue told a press conference here this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Asked to comment on China's anticipation on the 6th ASEAN
Regional Forum in Singapore later this month, Zhang said China
hopes that the forum would continue to proceed in a healthy
direction on the basis of equal participation, consultation and
progressing step by step.
</P>
<P>
China maintains that international norms, including the purpose
and guidelines of the UN Charter, should be emphasized under the
current international situation, the spokeswoman said.
</P>
<P>
Asked if the upcoming ARF would discuss the issue of South China
Sea, Zhang said that the issue should be settled through bilateral
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
China has always opposed discussing the South China Sea issue
on international occasions and China disagrees that the non-
related countries get involved in this issue, Zhang stated.
</P>
<P>
It would only make a bilateral issue more complicated if the
issue is internationalized, Zhang said, adding that China does not
think the ARF is an appropriate occasion to discuss the issue
concerning the South China Sea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
