<HEADLINE> Vietnam, U.S. Hope to Reach Trade Accord Soon: Spokeswoman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam and the United States hope
to promote the process of bilateral trade negotiations in order to
reach a trade agreement as soon as possible on the bases of
respecting each other's independence and sovereignty and equality
as well as mutual benefit, Vietnamese Foreign Ministry Spokeswoman
Phan Thay Thanh said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Thanh was answering questions about Vietnam-U.S. trade
negotiations at a press conference here Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
