<HEADLINE> Share Prices Plunge on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Share Prices plunged on the
Singapore Stock Market Thursday as investors continued to stay out
of the market and trade selectively.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) lost 20.91 points to
close at 2,157.72 points after a firmer opening on selective
buying in the morning session.
</P>
<P>
The volume increased to 536.28 million shares valued at 724.97
million Singapore dollars (about 426.88 million U.S. dollars).
Losers outstripped gainers by 341 to 26, more than 13 times, with
80 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Hotung topped the volume list with a turnover of 29.18 million
shares. It was followed by AFP that had 26.66 million units done.
GoldenAg was the next with 19.33 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SIA F led the gainers of the day picking up 50 cents to close
at 16.20 Singapore dollars. NatElec climbed up 30 cents to finish
at 8.10 Singapore dollars. Jar Str edged up 14 cents to end at
3.06 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, DBS and DBS F headed the descent losing 50
cents each to finish at 17.20 and 19.70 Singapore dollars
respectively. SPH, Seaview and UOB F sank 40 cents each to close
at 32.60, 8.50 and 12.50 Singapore dollars respectively. C &AMP; C
retreated 35 cents to end at 9.30 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said instead of bargain hunting, investors went after
quality stocks, albeit in a subdued manner, and there was no fresh
factors that could push up the stock market.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the market continued to be affected by the
remnants of the recent forced selling which started last week.
</P>
<P>
They also noted what pulled the index lower was some
profit-taking in stocks that rose recently despite the market
selling off. 
</P>
</TEXT>
