<HEADLINE> Air Route from Zhangjiajie to Macao to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- An air route from the city of
Zhangjiajie in central China's Hunan Province to Macao will be
opened on Saturday, Mayor Lu Pingyi of Zhangjiajie announced here
today.
</P>
<P>
On that day, a chartered plane will fly from Zhangjiajie to
Macao, Lu said at a press conference for the '99 China Ecological
Zhangjiajie Hunan International Forest Protection Festival to be
held in Zhangjiajie September 22 to 27.
</P>
<P>
He said that the new flight route will further facilitate
overseas tourism in Zhangjiajie, adding that he expected more than
100,000 tourists to visit the festival.
</P>
<P>
Situated in northwestern Hunan and in the heart of the
Wulingyuan Mountains, Zhangjiajie boosts unique and beautiful
natural scenery.
</P>
<P>
In 1982, Zhangjiajie was approved by the State Council as the
first State Forest Park in China, and the Wulingyuan scenic spot
was listed as a World Heritage site by UNESCO in 1992.
</P>
<P>
To date, Zhangjiajie has been linked by rail to most of the
major cities in China, and to more than 20 cities, including Hong
Kong, by air. 
</P>
</TEXT>
