<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Continue Surging in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Pushed by strong high-tech blue
chips, stock prices moved higher for another trading day in Tokyo
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average on the First Section of the
Tokyo Stock Exchange added 74.00 points, or 0.40 percent, to
Wednesday's close to end at 18,431.86, the highest closing so far
this year.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, rose 14.66 points or 0.98 percent to 1,511.
73, closing above 1,500.00 for the first time in almost two years.
</P>
<P>
High-priced technology issues continued attracting purchases,
supported partly by Wednesday's rise in the technology-heavy
Nasdaq composite index on Wall Street, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section came to 765.01 million shares,
almost unchanged from Wednesday's 766.06 million shares.
</P>
<P>
New Japan Securities Corp. was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers surpassed
gainers 637 to 557, with 131 shares ending unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
