President Giscard d'Estaing that he shorten his presidential term
from seven years to five years. He also called on the right-wing
opposition parties to stop quarreling and said the balance sheet
of his political coalition with Socialist Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin is positive.
</P>
<P>
-- African leaders failed to adopt a Nigeria-sponsored plan to
establish a system of group security on the continent haunted by
wars, as the summit of the Organization for African Unity (OAU)
ended on Wednesday in Algiers after three days of session focused
on preventing conflicts. Outgoing president of OAU, Burkina Faso's
president Blaise Compaore, gave a somber summary of the situation
in Africa before handing over his seat to Algerian President
Abdelaziz Bouteflika, the host of the summit.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The summit of OAU gave a surprising statement when it ended
on Wednesday in Algiers: "Coup d'Etat will no longer be tolerated.
" The OAU will not recognize from now anyone who takes power by
force, said the 38 leaders present at the summit, 21 of whom came
to power by arms -- either coup d'etat or war of liberation.
</P>
<P>
-- The U.N. Civil Administrator to Kosovo, Bernard Kouchner, is
due to arrive in Pristina on Thursday. Charged with re-
establishing the institutions, infrastructures and administration
in Kosovo, Kouchner has as his prior task to make ethnic Albanian
and Serb officials work together. 
