<HEADLINE> Red Tide Occurs In Waters Off Guangdong Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Personnel of the Nanhai Sub-
administration of the State Oceanic Administration found red tide
occur in areas off the east coastal of south China's Guangdong
Province on July 10, which was extended to some 10 sq km by
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first tide occur in waters off the province this
year.
</P>
<P>
From October 1997 to January 1998, extensive red tide occurred
over Zhelin Bay, the same waters at this time of the year, and it
has been twice caused by algae of the same category, which led to
huge losses for local fishery by producing toxins detrimental to
the survival of fish.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, no death of fish has been reported so far at this
initial stage in the water space where aquiculture is located. And
the density of red tide is forecasted to extend steadily and the
tide will possibly disappear in three to four days.
</P>
<P>
Local oceanic administration has sent special teams of
technicians to monitor the situation and make investigations on
the spot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
