<DOCNO> XIE19990715.0196 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Floods Kill Two in Ningxia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed and two
other are still missing in flooding caused by heavy rain on
Tuesday in Yanchi County in northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Local rainfall reached 120 millimeters in only two hours in the
early morning of July 13, with the ensuing floodwaters affecting
more than 60,000 people and causing 32 million yuan in direct
economic losses, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 13,000 head of livestock and poultry died in the
floods; more than 6,600 hectares of crops were ruined; 310 houses
collapsed; and many roads, bridges and water-control facilities
were demolished, authorities added.
</P>
<P>
The region has reported 16 incidents of hail, rainstorms, and
floods since late May which have affected 14 counties and seven
state-run farms and left three people dead.
</P>
<P>
The regional government has taken measures to help people in
the disaster areas and is also preparing to fight even larger
floods.  
</P>
</TEXT>
