<HEADLINE> Grand Mongolian Welcome for Chinese President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian President Nachagyn
Bagabandy held a grand welcoming ceremony in honor of visiting
Chinese President Jiang Zemin here Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
When President Jiang and his wife arrived at the Sukhebator
Square in downtown Ulan Bator, President Bagabandy and his wife
walked towards the Chinese guests and the two presidents shook
hands and greeted each other. Two Mongolian children, in
traditional Mongolian costumes, presented flowers to Jiang and his
wife.
</P>
<P>
After a military band played the national anthems of China and
Mongolia. Jiang and Bagabandy walked down the platform to inspect
the Mongolian state guards of honor.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the ceremony were members of Jiang's entourage,
including Vice Premier Qian Qichen and Vice Chairman of the
National People's Congress Standing Committee Buhe.
</P>
<P>
Mongolian officials, including Vice Chairman of the State Great
Hural Dogsomin Ganbold and Minister of External Relations Nyam-
Osorin Tuyaa, also attended the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived in the Mongolian capital earlier today for a
three-day state visit as the guest of Bagabandy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
