<HEADLINE> China, U.S. Begin Negotiation on Compensation of Embassy Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China and the United States have
started negotiation over compensation on the casualties and
damages of properties caused by the U.S.-led NATO's May 8 attack
of China's embassy in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, Chinese
Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue said here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
She confirmed the information at a routine press conference.
However, she didn't provide any details of the negotiation for "it
has just got started" as she said.
</P>
<P>
About a month ago, U.S. President's envoy and Undersecretary of
State Thomas Pickering came to Beijing and presented to the
Chinese government a U.S. government report on the results of its
investigation into the attack of the Chinese embassy in the
Federal Republic of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government declined the report as "unacceptable".
</P>
