<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fifty Thousand Drug Addicts Estimated in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 15 (Xinhua) -- There may be 50,000 drug
addicts in Kuwait, according to estimates by a British specialists
team at Kuwait's Psychological Disease Hospital.
</P>
<P>
David Mathews, a member of the team who arrived here three
years ago, said the estimation was based on the number of drug
addicts treated by the hospital each year, local English daily
Arab Times reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to Mathews, between 5,000 and 6,000 addicts visit the
hospital every year. International standards suggest that only 10
percent of the "problem cases" ever come to light.
</P>
<P>
"We are only seeing a fraction," Mathews said.
</P>
<P>
Unlike before the Iraqi invasion of Kuwait in 1990, when
alcohol was the drug of choice, today it is heroine that prevails,
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
