<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Issues Licenses to 3,862 Foreign Traders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Ministry of
Trade and Industry has issued licenses to 3,862 businessmen
engaged in the foreign trade sector so far this year, the
Ethiopian Herald newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ato Wolde Tsadiq, head of the ministry's registration and
licensing department, said here Wednesday that 4,607 trade
licenses have been renewed so far this year.
</P>
<P>
The licensed business persons have been engaged in various
foreign trade activities as exporter, importers, customs
transitors or trade agents, according to trade officials.
</P>
<P>
The National Bank of Ethiopia announced early this month that a
sum of 879 million U.S. dollars had been earned in foreign
currency during the previous fiscal year ending July 7, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The amount of the hard currency were earned from various
sectors of activity including foreign trade, foreign loans and
private dealings. 
