<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fresh Fighting Kills 12 in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Fresh fighting that broke out on
Wednesday between Sri Lankan government troops and Tamil rebels
left nine rebels and three soldiers killed in the north of the
country, the Defense Ministry said Thursday in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The troops destroyed a rebel bunker with grenades and machine
guns north of Kalyanapura, killing five rebels, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
However, three soldiers were killed as the rebels retaliated
with mortars, it said.
</P>
<P>
The troops on Wednesday also killed three rebels in two other
separate clashes in the Jaffna area.
</P>
<P>
The troops sniped and killed another rebel in the Wanni area,
it added.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, a bomb set off by Tamil rebels killed two
civilians and injured 28 others including five police personnel in
Batticaloa, 300 kilometers east of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The blast came as security forces and police remained on red
alert against Tamil rebels' attacks at a time when the rebels were
celebrating the 12th anniversary of their first suicide bomb
attack.
</P>
<P>
Tamil rebels have been battling the Sri Lankan government since
1983 for a homeland for Tamil minorities in the north and east of
the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
