<HEADLINE> China Opens Copper Trade Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China's first copper trade center,
the Anhui Copper Trade Center, opened formally in the city of
Tongling, a major copper producer in east China's Anhui Province,
recently.
</P>
<P>
The center, covering an area of 27,000 sq m, will focus on
trading of various copper products ranging from copper concentrate,
copper wire to copper handicraft articles.
</P>
<P>
Trading in the form of futures, spot and contracted
transactions will be carried out at the trade center.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than 40 enterprises have participated in the trade,
with combined turnover topping one billion yuan (120 million US
dollars) in the first five months.
</P>
<P>
The center, with the approval of China's State Development
Planning Commission, aims to become a national copper exchange.
</P>
</TEXT>
