<DOCNO> XIE19990715.0233 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Habibie Says He'll Support Megawati if She's Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President B.J. Habibie
will welcome Megawati Soekarnoputri, leader of the Indonesian
Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI-P), as new president if the
People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) elects her in the upcoming
session.
</P>
<P>
This was stated by Minister of Justice/State Secretary Muladi
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"If 700 members of the MPR, most of them elect Megawati (to be
president) constitutionally, it means God want her being
president. People have to support her," Muladi said before
attending a hearing with the House of Representatives Commission I
on law and foreign affairs.
</P>
<P>
Muladi, however, said that in vice versa situation, if the MPR
elects incumbent president Habibie, he has the support from the
people.
</P>
<P>
"Just let the members of the MPR make decision," Muladi added.
</P>
<P>
In a weekend interview with Singapore's Straits Times newspaper
in Jakarta, Habibie said he would accept Megawati, daughter of
Indonesia's founding president Soekarno, as president if the MPR
appointed her.
</P>
<P>
"If people want to have her, then I will accept it because I
have full confidence that the people will take the best," The
Indonesian Observer Thursday quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
The contest for the presidency will be decided by the MPR,
which incorporates the 500-member parliament and 200 provincial
and community appointees. Habibie, who has been nominated for the
presidency by the ruling Golkar Party, is in competition with
Megawati.
</P>
<P>
The MPR, the country's highest decision-making body, will meet
in November to elect the country's next president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990715.0234 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Firms in Guangdong Export More </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Private companies of south China
's Guangdong Province did 94.512 million U.S. dollars worth of
imports and exports from January to June this year, 4.6 times the
figure for the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
In breakdown, exports reached 34.105 million U.S. dollars
during the first half of the year, double the figure for the same
period last year, whereas imports amounted to 60.407 million U.S.
dollars, 13.5 times the figure for the first six months last year.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the province now boasted some 2,000
export-oriented private businesses, of which, 15 are authorized by
the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC) to
do foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Locally-produced commodities in the province are exported to 83
countries and regions. And 38.3 percent of China's total foreign
trade volume were accomplished by Guangdong's foreign trade
companies.
</P>
<P>
As a major step to rejuvenate and reform its foreign trade
system, which has long been dominated by state-owned companies,
MOFTEC started to grant private firms the right to do foreign
trade late last year. So far, 142 private companies have been
granted the right and are now competing with state-owned companies
in foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
To obtain the license to do foreign trade, applicants (private
businesses) are required to have registered capital of at least 8.
50 million yuan (approximately one million US dollars) and an
annual turnover of 50 million yuan (6 million US dollars).
Electronic firms must have an annual turnover of at least 30
million yuan (3.6 million US dollars), with the figure for
machinery standing at 10 million yuan (1.2 million US dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
