<HEADLINE> Garbage Processing in Industrial City Gets Overseas Funding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Anshan, an industrial city in
northeast China's Liaoning province, has recently received 2.1
billion Korean won (about 1.8 million US dollars) of loans from
the government of the Republic of Korea as funding for a garbage
processing project.
</P>
<P>
"The loans will greatly accelerate the pace of building the
garbage processing plant and help the city government solve the
headache of disposing garbage and making recycled use of the waste,
" said Li Shikai, vice-mayor of Anshan.
</P>
<P>
As a famous heavy industrial city in northeast China, Anshan is
home to the first steel plant in New China of Anshan Steel and
Iron Complex. Garbage disposal has always been taken as a top
priority for the city, which has a population of more than 3.2
million.
</P>
<P>
The Anshan branch of the Bank of China acted as the sub-lender
of the overseas loans.  
</P>
