<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Rare Birds Born in Northwest China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Two baby black-necked cranes, a
rare species in the world, have been born in Xining Zoo, the
capital of northwest China's Qinghai Province, bringing the total
number in the zoo to 18.
</P>
<P>
Black-necked crane, the most precious of the 15 kinds of
cranes in the world, has been listed as an endangered species and
is now under top protection in China.
</P>
<P>
Qinghai is the homeland of black-necked crane. crane flocks
migrated to Ngoring and Gyaring lakes in central Qinghai from the
Yunnan-Guizhou Plateau for propagation in Spring and return to the
south in October every year.
</P>
<P>
The first pair of baby black-necked cranes were born in Xining
after a three-year experiment of trial reproduction. The city has
so far given 12 gifted cranes to zoos in Shanghai, Shenzhen and
other cities and are doing well there.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990715.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group Ends 36th Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison
Group concluded its 36th session here on Wednesday after
conducting a range of negotiations on Macao's smooth transition
and the transfer of power from Portugal to China.
</P>
<P>
Han Zhaokang, chief representative of the Chinese team of the
liaison group, said the two-day session was the last but second
liaison meeting in the preparatory process of the Macao handover
and also the last such meeting held in Lisbon.
</P>
<P>
He said the meeting was a positive and fruitful one as both
sides had attached great importance to it and made adequate
preparations in advance.
</P>
<P>
Han told reporters that Macao's handover has only about five
months to go. Both the Chinese and Portuguese sides shoulder great
responsibilities for the last-stage groundwork and have felt a
great sense of urgency.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed at the meeting that they should handle
matters related to the transition and the transfer of power of
Macao in a positive and business-like manner.
</P>
<P>
He said that all open questions will and should be solved as
long as both sides make joint efforts while taking into account
the overall situation of the smooth transition and give overriding
attention to bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Antonio Santana Carlos, chief representative of the Portuguese
side of the Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group, said that the
meeting was quite successful and reaped concrete achievements. He
hoped both sides would speed up negotiations on questions yet to
be agreed upon.
</P>
<P>
He said the liaison group will hold an informal meeting at
Portugal's Acores Islands from July 15 to 17.
</P>
<P>
The 37th, or the last session, of the Sino-Portuguese Joint
Liaison Group is scheduled for November 9-10 in Macao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
