<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Arrives in Mongolia on State Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
arrived in the Mongolian capital of Ulan Bator Thursday morning on
a three-day state visit at the invitation of Mongolian President
Nachagyn Bagabandy.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's one-nation tour, a reciprocal one of Bagabandy's state
visit to China last December, is an important visit to Mongolia
paid by the Chinese head of state at the juncture of two centuries.
</P>
<P>
Landing at the airport at 11:30 a.m. local time (3:30 GMT),
Jiang and his wife, Wang Yeping, were warmly welcomed by Nyam-
Osorin Tuyaa, Mongolian minister of external relations and
Mongolian ambassador to China Dagva Tsakhilgaan.
</P>
<P>
In a written speech at the airport, Jiang said, "I am paying
the visit on the eve of the 50th anniversary of the establishment
of diplomatic relations between China and Mongolia. I would like
to avail myself of this opportunity to convey cordial greetings
and sincere regards from the Chinese people to the friendly
Mongolian people."
</P>
<P>
He said that as close neighbors, both countries and their
peoples have long enjoyed traditional good-neighborly friendship
and cooperation. Recent years have witnessed continuous expansion
and development of such friendly cooperation in such fields as
politics, the economy, trade, education and culture.
</P>
<P>
He said China has always attached great importance to its
relations with Mongolia and that it is China's firm policy to
further consolidate and develop a long-term stable, sound and
mutually trusting Sino-Mongolian relationship of good-neighborly
cooperation geared toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Jiang is scheduled to meet with President
Bagabandy, other Mongolian leaders and people from all walks of
life to exchange views on bilateral ties and issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
"I believe the visit will further promote the mutual
understanding and trust between both countries and bring bilateral
bonds smoothly into the 21st century," said the president.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's entourage arriving on the same plane include Vice
Premier Qian Qichen and his wife, Zhou Hanqiong, Vice-Chairman of
the National People's Congress Standing Committee Buhe, Deputy
Director of the General Office of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) You Xigui, Vice Minister of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation Chen Xinhua, Director of the
President's Office Jia Ting'an and Assistant Foreign Minister Wang
Yi.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and his wife were also greeted at the airport by Chinese
Ambassador to Mongolia Qi Zhijia, Qi's wife, Wang Shuying, as well
as representatives from the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia and
Chinese institutions, and students studying here.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
