<HEADLINE> China to Set Up Local Insurance Regulatory Offices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The national insurance market
watchdog China Insurance Regulatory Commission (CIRC) will open
local offices within two years to strengthen industry supervision,
officials said here today.
</P>
<P>
CIRC officials said the local regulatory offices will be set up
in all the provincial capital cities, and the State Council, the
country's highest governing body, has given its go-ahead to the
plan.
</P>
<P>
The first local CIRC offices would be operational as early as
later this year, they said.
</P>
<P>
An official quoted CIRC Vice-Chairman Wu Dingfu as saying
recently that the CIRC Beijing office would be operational before
the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The CIRC was established in November 1998 by the State Council
to supervise the insurance market. It has yet to set up its local
offices.  
</P>
</TEXT>
