<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, July 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The International Finance Corporation (IFC)
announced Wednesday that it has launched a South African rand 100
million borrowing (approximately 16.3 million U.S. dollars) under
its Global Medium Term Note program.
</P>
<P>
The 5-year notes carry a coupon of 13.75 percent and an issue
price of 101.025 percent. The proceeds of the issue were swapped
into U.S. dollar floating rate funds. The lead manager was Toronto
Dominion Securities, London. (IFC-Notes Offering)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Brazil's grain harvest during the 1998-1999 period
will be 82.117 million tons, 7.3 percent higher than the 1997-1998
period, said Minister of Agriculture Francisco Turra Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The National Supply Company associated with the Ministry of
Agriculture estimated that the bean harvest will increase by 34.7
percent over last year and the rice harvest by 35.3 percent. (
Brazil-Grain-Harvest)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANIERO -- Brazil's largest state-run company, Petrobras,
has decided to issue one billion U.S. dollars bonds on the
international market in the near future, local press quoted the
company's chief as saying on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"We are going to issue the share offer if market conditions are
correct and the price is acceptable," said Petrobras President
Philippe Reichstul. (Brazil-Bonds)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- The Venezuelan oil basket price this week reached 16.
8 U.S. dollars per barrel, a rise of 36 cents as compared with the
price at the close of trading last week, according to the Ministry
of Energy and Mines on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Last week the price rose by 1.55 dollars from 14.89 to 16.44
dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
The price rise came at a time when the sale and demand of
petroleum products are tending to equilibrium. (Venezuela-Oil
Price)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- Chile's copper production will account for 42
percent of the world's total in 1999, president of the State
Copper Corporation Marcos Lima said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He said that Chile will produce 4.2 million tons of copper, of
which 1.6 million tons will come from CODELCO, the largest copper
mining company in the world. Global copper production will be 10
million tons in 1999. (Santiago-Copper)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- The cost for restructuring and recapitalizing the
country's battered banking sector was estimated at 550 trillion
rupiah (about 82 billion U.S. dollars), or about 50 percent of the
gross domestic product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
Minister of Finance Bambang Subianto said the burden to the
state budget in the next fiscal year beginning from April 2000
would be much higher than the 34 trillion rupiah (about 5.07
billion dollars) allocated in the current 1999/2000 budget. (
Indonesia-Bank Recapitalization)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Thailand's automobile market has shown an marked
improvement as sales in the first half of this year increased 21
percent to 85,000 units, The Nation reported here Thursday.
