The BMA hopes to attract foreign tourists to stay longer in
Bangkok, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
In the past, most foreign tourists usually spent only a few
days before heading to other destinations.
</P>
<P>
The BMA is in the process of improving the environment and
tourist sites as well as appointing personnel to assist tourists
at many places.
</P>
<P>
The activities will start in October this year and will
continue until the end of 2000.
</P>
<P>
The BMA hopes that the campaign will result in an income of 200
billion baht (5.4 billion U.S. dollars) from both local and
foreign tourists, the press release said. 
