<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Assists Development of Northwest Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank has provided 650
million U.S. dollars in loans for northwest China's Gansu Province
in the past 14 years, greatly spurring the province's economic and
social progress.
</P>
<P>
The loans were mainly used in the sectors of agriculture, water
control, forestry, education, public health and transportation,
said local authorities.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank-assisted projects provided irrigation for nearly
30,000 hectares of drought-stricken farmland in the province,
curbed the losses of water and soil erosion in Guanchuan river
valley, enabled 14 counties to popularize the junior middle school
education and provided potable water for a population of more than
1.3 million.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank has cooperated well with Gansu and the sound
links are expected to continue, a World Bank authority said.
</P>
</TEXT>
