<HEADLINE> Pudong Reports Continued Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 15 (Xinhua)-- The number of foreign-funded
businesses in the Pudong New Zone of Shanghai, has reached 5,630
since its establishment nine years ago.
</P>
<P>
The zone has attracted a total investment of over 28 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
An official from the zone's management said that investment for
each of the foreign-funded projects averages 4.98 million US
dollars and that nearly 80 percent of the projects have investment
of over 10 million US dollars each.
</P>
<P>
He said that over 90 of the world's top 500 companies have
invested in Pudong.
</P>
<P>
Observers say that Pudong's attractiveness lies in its sound
legal structure and its uncompromising fight against violations of
intellectual property rights.
</P>
<P>
Pudong management's efficiency in handing investors' request is
another strong aspect that foreign investors value.  
</P>
