<HEADLINE> China Further Refutes Cox Report (6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"It is typical racial discrimination, and a deadly insult to
the Chinese nation that the Cox Report links the so-called
espionage activities with China's policies and guidelines for
developing science and technology, the research institutes and
their staff engaging in bilateral scientific and technological
exchanges, the business agencies and their staff engaging in
economic and trade exchanges, the official and non-official
Chinese representative offices and their staff in the United
States, American Chinese and Chinese students in the United States,
" Zhao said.
</P>
<P>
"It marks the reappearance of McCarthyism, active in the United
States in 1950s, and reflects the aberrant personality of some
American politicians hostile to China's development and becoming
powerful," he added.
</P>
<P>
Zhao pointed out that the Cox Report listed many data, which
were either intentionally fabricated or painstakingly distorted.
Although it could whip up public opinion and hoodwink some people
for a while, it could not do so for long.
</P>
<P>
"For a period of time, some politicians in the United States
have clung on to the out-dated Cold War mentality, and made an
issue out of Sino-U.S. relations by stirring up an anti-China mood
to reap political profit," Zhao said, "Years of practice have
proved that the healthy development of Sino-U.S. relations
coincide with the fundamental interests of the peoples of the two
countries."
</P>
<P>
"It is really dishonorable for some U.S. politicians trying
hard to undermine Sino-U.S. relations by fabricating lies," he
said, "But, it is impossible for them to succeed."
</P>
<P>
The Information Office of the State Council also released an
article at the press conference entitled "Facts Speak Louder Than
Words and Lies Will Collapse by Themselves -- Further Refutation
of the Cox Report". The article contains eight parts with more
than 20,000 Chinese characters. 
</P>
