<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Army, Police Arrest 132 in Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan Army and police
arrested 132 suspected Tamil rebels in a major cordon-and-search
operation in the capital city of Colombo Wednesday, informed
sources said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the operation was conducted on security
information that a group of Tamil rebels had arrived in Colombo
with a large consignment of arms and ammunition to attack prime
targets in the city.
</P>
<P>
A large number of Tamil youths from the north and the east of
the country who recently arrived in Colombo were among those
arrested, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a war against the government
for a separate state in the north and east of the island since
1983. 
