<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Oil Basket Price Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Venezuelan oil basket price
this week reached 16.8 U.S. dollars per barrel, a rise of 36 cents
as compared with the price at the close of trading last week,
according to the Ministry of Energy and Mines on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Last week the price rose by 1.55 dollars from 14.89 to 16.44
dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
The price rise came at a time when the sale and demand of
petroleum products are tending to equilibrium.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, the average price of the Venezuelan oil
basket has been 12.02 dollars per barrel, which is 3.02 dollars
above the sale price estimated in the Nation's budget for 1999.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Venezuelan petroleum sector believed that the
tendency to a strengthening of the oil price is now certain, after
the big fall registered between the end of 1997 and February of
this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
