<HEADLINE> Brazil's Top Company to Issue One Billion Dollars Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANIERO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's largest state-run
company, Petrobras, has decided to issue one billion U.S. dollars
bonds on the international market in the near future, local press
quoted the company's chief as saying on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"We are going to issue the share offer if market conditions are
correct and the price is acceptable," said Petrobras President
Philippe Reichstul.
</P>
<P>
Petrobras is in a process of adjusting its financial structure
to have a closer relationship with the market, such as creating
new sectors which have intensified market-oriented links.
</P>
<P>
The recent disturbance in the Latin American market, which was
due to the possible delay of Argentina's repayment of external
debt, has affected some Brazilian companies hoping to issue bonds
in the international market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
