<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile to Account for 42 Percent of World Copper Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Chile's copper production will
account for 42 percent of the world's total in 1999, president of
the State Copper Corporation Marcos Lima said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He said that Chile will produce 4.2 million tons of copper, of
which 1.6 million tons will come from CODELCO, the largest copper
mining company in the world. Global copper production will be 10
million tons in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Chile is the largest copper producer in the world, earning 40
percent of the country's foreign revenue, even though the price
has fallen to the lowest level this year in a decade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
