<HEADLINE> Gansu Earmarks 1.6 Billion Yuan for Poverty Relief Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu province
has decided to allocate an additional one billion yuan to its
poverty-relief efforts, boosting its total financial support to
nearly 1.6 billion yuan this year.
</P>
<P>
With the huge funding, the provincial government will be able
to reach its goal of providing adequate food and clothing for 800,
000 people living in poverty through various development projects.
</P>
<P>
When the government officially launched its poverty-relief
campaign in 1983, this inland province's impoverished population
stood at 12.54 million.
</P>
<P>
After 16 years of hard work, the provincial government has been
successful in getting more than 10 million people out of poverty.
</P>
<P>
Now the number of people living in poverty has dropped to 1.77
million or 8.8 percent of its population, compared to 74.8 percent
in 1983.
</P>
<P>
With this year's record-high financial support, the province
will try to help 20 of its poverty-stricken counties to provide
adequate food and clothing for their people, including the seven
counties in Hexi and Dingxi areas, according to provincial
government sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
