<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shandong Having Success With Imported Fruit Trees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- A research institute at the Shandong
Academy of Agricultural Sciences has opened its demonstration area
for fruit trees grown from imported seeds.
</P>
<P>
The area, set up Tuesday, is the 10th state-level center in
China for experimenting with imported agricultural technology and
developments.
</P>
<P>
Shandong is one of China's major agricultural areas. It started
the demonstration project in 1997 and now has 35 of these areas
that are recognized by local governments.
</P>
<P>
Shandong has earned nearly 1.9 billion yuan annually from
growing improved fruit from trees grown from imported seeds on
over 33,000 hectares of land. It has also sent specialists and
technicians abroad to study developments there and has imported
more than 30 varieties of seeds that are suited to Chinese
conditions.
</P>
<P>
The province gives priority to using bio-technology for genetic
improvements that prevent disease, make fruit trees blossom
earlier than usual, and prolong the yield period of trees.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
