<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Hits Eastern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 15 (Xinhua) -- A moderate earthquake measuring 4.8
on the Richter scale jolted the Ibaraki and Chiba prefectures in
eastern Japan on Thursday morning, the Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
Neither immediate reports of damages and casualties nor tsunami
and tidal wave warnings was issued as yet.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake, which occurred at 7:56 a.m. (local
time), was estimated to be 70 kilometers underground in the
southern part of the Ibaraki Prefecture, the agency said. 
</P>
