<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Communist Party Leader Ends Visit to Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- General Secretary of the Communist
Party of Vietnam Le Kha Phieu concluded his first seven-day
official visit to Cuba on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Le held talks with Cuban President Fidel
Castro on bilateral and international issues.
</P>
<P>
In a joint declaration signed Tuesday, the two leaders
expressed satisfaction with the development and consolidation of
cooperation and friendship between the two countries, two parties
and two peoples.
</P>
<P>
They voiced strong opposition to NATO's new strategic
conception, describing it as "hegemonic". They also condemned its
aggression against Yugoslavia and urged respect for the role of
the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
They called for a new international economic order, saying that
the current economic order harms the interests of the developing
countries.
</P>
<P>
Le, on behalf of the Vietnamese government and people, donated
3,000 tons of rice to Cuba. 
</P>
</TEXT>
