<HEADLINE> Panama to Remain Vigilant on Border Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Incoming Panamanian Director
of the National Police Carlos Bares said here Wednesday that
Panama will remain vigilant on the security along the border with
Colombia.
</P>
<P>
Panama recently mobilized over 1,000 policemen to the border
amidst allegations of a rise in border incursions and the
kidnapping of Panamanian citizens by Colombian guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Bares, designated by president-elect Mireya Moscoso, denied
that there would be any change in the border policies toward
Colombia after the new cabinet is sworn in on September 1.
</P>
<P>
Moscoso traveled to Colombia recently to discuss the issue of
border security with the Colombian authorities.
</P>
<P>
Panama and Colombia have set up a mechanism of maintaining
border security through dialogue. 
