<HEADLINE> Philippines to Bid for 2003 SEA Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Olympic Council (POC)
intends to bid for the 2003 Southeast Asian (SEA) Games and "equal
or even surpass the achievements of the 1991 Manila SEA Games."
</P>
<P>
The POC Executive Council unanimously endorsed the proposal to
host the biennial event on Wednesday. The POC President Celso
Dayrit said the council will draft a resolution asking Philippine
President Joseph Estrada to support the POC's offer.
</P>
<P>
Dayrit said the country could "even do better than the 91 gold
medals and the second place overall we achieved in the 1991 SEA
Games in Manila."
</P>
<P>
Once they are able to get the government's endorsement, Dayrit
said they will formalize their bid during the SEA Games Federation
Council meeting on August 5 in Brunei, two days before the formal
opening of the 20th edition of the meet.
</P>
<P>
"Unless either Vietnam or Laos make a formal offer, according
to alphabetical order, it should be our turn to host the SEA Games
in 2003," Dayrit said.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is already committed for the 2001 SEA Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
