<HEADLINE> Zambia Cut down Number of Participants to All African Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Zambia Olympics Commonwealth and
All African Games Associaltion (ZOCAGA) has trimmed the number of
participants to the All African Games held in September this year
in South Africa from 119 to between 50 and 60 because of money
shortage.
</P>
<P>
Sports, Youth and Child Development Abel Chambeshi said here
Wednesday that the government have no that kind of money and
therefore had to cut down the number so that reasonable figures
could be found taking into consideration past performance of those
to travel.
</P>
<P>
The government has very little resources to send a team to
South Africa and it will not be in the interest of the country to
send people whose track record is poor or who have not been
practising at all for the events, he said.
</P>
<P>
Chambeshi also said that he will go to Cuba in September this
year to source for equipment and manpower to rekinndle boxing in
his country.
</P>
<P>
Cuba is a powerhouse in boxing and it is for this reason that "
we want to see what help they can give us in terms of equipment
and manpower," the minister said. 
</P>
