<HEADLINE> Bayern Beats Dortmund to Enter League Cup Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Germany defender Christian Woerns
scored an own goal to bring Bayern Munich past arch-rivals
Borussia Dortmund 1-0 in Augsburg on Wednesday for reach the final
of the German League Cup.
</P>
<P>
German champions Bayern, entering the traditional six-team pre-
season tournament from the semi-finals, won despite the absence
through injury of six first-choice players.
</P>
<P>
The only goal came in the 66th minute when Woerns, who joined
Dortmund from Paris St Germain, diverted a free kick from Bayern
playmaker and new captain Stefan Effenberg into his own net.
</P>
<P>
Bayern, who have won the tournament for the last two years,
will face Werder Bremen in Saturday's final in Leverkusen.
</P>
<P>
Werder, who beat Bayern on penalties in the German Cup final
last month, beat Bayer Leverkusen 2-1 in the other semi-final on
Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
