<HEADLINE> Hungary Wins Men's Team Relay in Pentathlon Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Hungarian team of Akos
Hanzely, Peter Sarfalvi and Gabor Balogh won the men's team relay
final in the Modern Pentathlon World Championships on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarians opened a lead in shooting, and went on to win
the fencing, as well. They were not among the top teams in
swimming and riding, but still had an overall lead of 118 points
over the Americans after four events.
</P>
<P>
Hungary started the running event with an advantage of 29
seconds ahead of the United States and another 20 seconds ahead of
Russia.
</P>
<P>
Defending world champion Germany finished 10th. 
</P>
