<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0045GMT, July 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States Wednesday urged parties in the
British province of Northern Ireland to put aside their
differences and President Bill Clinton is ready to help when
necessary.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a regular briefing, White House spokesman Joe
Lockhart reiterated that the April 1998 Good Friday accord to end
the conflict in Northern Ireland should not be allowed to collapse.
</P>
<P>
"The president remains ready to intervene in any way... the
parties believe will move the process forward," Lockhart said.(US-
Ireland)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GENEVA -- The United Nations will send a team of experts to
Yugoslavia next week to evaluate environmental damage caused by
NATO's 11-week military attacks against the country, U.N.
officials announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
About a dozen of experts will begin their study in Belgrade on
July 19 and then split up to work in the Kosovo capital of
Pristina and in Pancevo, an industrial town where an oil refinery
and petrochemical plant were hit by NATO bombs.(UN-Environment-
Yugoslavia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa on Wednesday
spoke highly of a recent meeting between Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak and his Sudanese counterpart Omar al-Bashir.
</P>
<P>
"The meeting is a key step on the way to progress of the
bilateral ties," Moussa told Egypt's Middle East News Agency on
the sidelines of the 35th summit of the Organization of African
Unity (OAU) in the Algerian capital of Algiers.
</P>
<P>
He voiced hope that the two countries "would maintain good
cooperation in the near future." (Egypt-Sudan-Summit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India's caretaker Prime Minister Atal Behari
Vajpayee Wednesday asked Pakistan to restart Lahore peace process,
which began last February when he and Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif signed the Lahore Declaration.
</P>
<P>
The Lahore Declaration was a "firm commitment between India and
Pakistan to resolve all issues bilaterally and what happened in
Kargil (of Kashmir) was totally against this commitment," Vajpayee
said at a public rally in Kulu, a northern city.(India-Pakistan-
Peace Process)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GENEVA -- The International Air Transport Association (IATA)
urged NATO here Tuesday to immediately lift flight ban over the
Kosovo region.
</P>
<P>
"At least 30 percent of the increased air traffic control
delays in the last three months have been caused by diverting
civilian flights around the Kosovo region into Italy, France and
Eastern Europe," the IATA said in a statement.(IATA-NATO-No-fly
Zones) 
</P>
