<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment Surges in East China Port City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The coastal city of Qingdao in
east China's Shandong Province approved 301 new overseas-funded
projects in the first half this year, involving 820 million U.S.
dollars of overseas investment, a rise of 6.7 percent and 87.9
percent on a yearly basis respectively.
</P>
<P>
The figures show a bigger scale of the ventures than those set
up a year earlier. According to local sources, 25 of the new
overseas-funded projects each had an investment of more than 10
million U.S. dollars. The big projects were centered on the fields
of household apparatus, chemicals, and machine buildings.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment in local agriculture and service sectors
also climbed up remarkably.
</P>
<P>
During the six-month period, the inflow of overseas money from
Asia doubled that a year earlier, with the amount from the
European Union rising 160 percent year on year and the figure from
the U.S. soaring 170 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong topped a list of overseas investors in terms of the
investment locally during the first half of the year, followed by
the U.S., the Republic of Korea, Japan and Denmark.  
</P>
</TEXT>
