<HEADLINE> Chilean Chamber of Deputies Urges Banning Nazi Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Chilean Chamber of Deputies
on Wednesday called on President Eduardo Frei to ban a Nazi
conference in Chile, slated for April 2000.
</P>
<P>
The call came alongside a move by the chamber to pass a law
prohibiting the existence of Nazi groups within the country.
</P>
<P>
The chamber held that the "totalitarian character of Nazism as
an ideology which promotes hatred and racism" is incompatible with
the country's democratic and republican tradition and is in
contradiction with human dignity.
</P>
<P>
The First Ideological Meeting of the National Socialists was
scheduled for April 15-22, 2000.
</P>
<P>
Last Sunday, several hundred Jews marched in the center of
Santiago, urging the parliament to approve the anti-discrimination
law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
