<HEADLINE> Indonesia, Portugal to Meet at U.N. on East Timor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials of
Indonesia and Portugal will meet at the U.N. Headquarters in New
York on Thursday and Friday to review developments related to a
vote on the future of East Timor, the U.N. announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Jamsheed Marker, Personal Representative of the U.N.
Secretary-General for East Timor will chair the talks, U.N.
spokesman Manoel de Almeida e Silva said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia will be led by Nugroho Wisnumurti, Director General
of Political Affairs of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the
Portugal will be led by Fernando Neves, Director General for
Special Political Questions at the Portuguese Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
"They will go over peace and reconciliation efforts in the
territory and will discuss post ballot issues," the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
Under the mandate given by an agreement between Indonesia and
Portugal on May 5, the United Nations is organizing and conducting
a "popular consultation" or ballot in East Timor to see whether
the majority of the 800,000 East Timorese want special autonomy
with Indonesia or independence.
</P>
<P>
The original vote date was set for August 8, but U.N.
Secretary-General Kofi Annan delayed it by two weeks last month
for security concerns and better logistics preparations.
</P>
<P>
He also postponed vote registration by 3 days until Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The May 5 accord provides for a solution to the dispute between
Indonesia and Portugal over the status of East Timor, a Portuguese
colony until 1975.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia occupied it after a civil rift took place in 1975. It
made the territory a province the following year and since then
the U.N. has been seeking a solution to the status of the
"non-self-governing territory" administered by Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
In January, Jakarta put forward a special autonomy package
for East Timor, saying that if the majority of the local people
would like to part, Indonesia will not oppose.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
