<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Five Russian large landing ships
carrying 450 soldiers, 130 armored vehicles and about 100 tons of
food arrived in the northern Greek port of Thessaloniki Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian peacekeeping force's disembarkation process is
expected to be completed by late Wednesday night, and their
transport to Macedonia, to be followed by Kosovo, will begin on
Thursday morning, the Thessaloniki-based Macedonian Press Agency
(MPA) reported.
</P>
