<HEADLINE> Keane Rejects Contract Offer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Roy Keane has rejected Manchester
United's offer of an extended contract and has repeated his threat
to leave if the club does not meet the player's terms.
</P>
<P>
The Republic of Ireland midfielder is waiting for a new offer
from the club after the he turned down the initial contract
presented to him at the end of last month.
</P>
<P>
Keane, who has one year left on his current contract, could
leave the club next summer as a free transfer under the Bosman
ruling.
</P>
<P>
"If the new contract is not right then I won't sign it," said
the 27-year-old.
</P>
<P>
"I won't undersell myself. I would think that this is my last
big contract so it has got to be right.
</P>
<P>
"Even though I am United's captain, have moved into a new house
and my family are settled here, I won't sign a deal I am not happy
with.
</P>
<P>
"If it isn't sorted out I will have to look at the bigger
picture and I would be prepared to go. That's not a threat, that's
just life," added Keane.
</P>
<P>
Keane, who has not gone on the club tour of Australia, China
and Hong Kong of China, is reported to have asked for two million
pounds a season.
</P>
<P>
The Irishman is currently suffering from a recurrence of his
ankle injury and is likely to miss the Charity Shield against
Arsenal on August 1.
</P>
<P>
"I'm pretty confident I will be fine for the opening
Premiership match at Everton, that's my priority," said Keane.
</P>
<P>
Denis Irwin will skipper United in Keane's absence in their
first pre-season tour match against Australia in Melbourne on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Australian-born Mark Bosnich will make his first appearance for
United since rejoining the club last month on a free transfer from
Aston Villa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
