<HEADLINE> Ferguson Not Keen on Robbie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- English Premier League soccer club
Manchester United manager Sir Alex Ferguson has blasted Aston
Villa boss John Gregory's bid to buy teenage prodigy Robbie Keane
from Wolves.
</P>
<P>
Gregory is hoping to push through a six million pounds deal for
the Republic of Ireland international this week but the Manchester
United boss said he would only consider taking the youngster to
Old Trafford if he was available at 500,000 pounds and then he
would only be a reserve.
</P>
<P>
"At six million pounds, I would not go near the player," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"If he was 500,000 pounds and could spend time in our second
team I might have a look. But at that price Aston Villa can have
him."
</P>
<P>
Sir Alex's extraordinary tirade is the latest clash between him
and Gregory, which began over United's on-off 12.5 million pounds
signing of Dwight Yorke and continued earlier this year when the
Villa boss predicted United had no chance of winning their
historic Treble.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile Ferguson named eight Arsenal players when asked to
pick his all-star Premiership side (excluding his own charges).
</P>
<P>
The United boss chose David Seaman, Martin Keown, Tony Adams,
Nigel Winterburn, Emmanuel Petit, Patrick Vieira, Marc Overmars
and Dennis Bergkamp as well as Chelsea's Albert Ferrer, Tottenham'
s Darren Anderton and Michael Owen, of Liverpool. 
</P>
