<HEADLINE> Dow Falls But Other Indexes Rise On Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NEW YORK, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial
average moved lower Wednesday as investors took profits from the
big gains in recent trading sessions.
</P>
<P>
The blue chip stocks closed down 26.92 at 11,148.10, adding
to its 26 point drop Tuesday. The Dow was also dragged lower by
fears of political tensions in Asia provoked by the Taiwanese
leader's separatist remarks and concerns about worsening
economic situation in Latin America.
</P>
<P>
But the technology heavy Nasdaq index was pushed higher by a
tame inflation report and a strong earnings outlook from
computer chip maker Intel. The index rose 39.90 at 2,818.13,
surpassing the record closing high of 2,793.07, set last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Commerce Department said retail sales rose just 0.1
percent in June while the Labor Department reported the Producer
Price Index fell a smaller-than-expected 0.1 percent in the same
month. Intel said late Tuesday its second-quarter earnings
jumped 49 percent.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index rose 4.61 at 1,398.17 and the NYSE index rose
1.26 at 654.90.
</P>
<P>
The American Stock Exchange index rose 0.67 at 813.00 and
the Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 3.35 at 461.46.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 10-to-9 margin
on the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,536 up, 1,398 down and
602 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 745.53 million shares from 733.78
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
