<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eating While Watch TV Bad For Health, Italian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, 14 July (Xinhua) -- Two out of three Italian families eat
dinner while watching television, causing them to eat more as well
as to have digestive problems, Italian health experts said.
</P>
<P>
A survey, which was carried out by Italian market research
company IMS, said that up to 80 percent of single people ate and
watched TV at the same time.
</P>
<P>
Daniela Marafante, one of fifty health experts questioned by
the research company, said that people who watch television while
eating pay less attention to the food they are about to eat.
</P>
<P>
"Television leads people to eat more than they should, as it
tends to anesthetize them," she explained.
</P>
<P>
And according to Michele Carruba, president of Italy's national
health and science organization, "watching television makes it
impossible to realize that you are full."
</P>
<P>
Explaining why many people eat whenever they sit down in front
of their television sets, Raffaele Morelli, editor of a health
magazine said: "TV activates a process of association between
eating and watching a film, in the same way that some people link
coffee with a cigarette." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
